<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">sources</ENAMEX> say this is a coded way of threatening a nuclear response .

            
Because a ban can be easily circumvented
(chemical <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT_DESC">weapons</ENAMEX> can be produced from everyday products without elaborate
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">facilities</ENAMEX>), the treaty installs a sweeping verification program ,
originally proposed during the <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Reagan</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">administration</ENAMEX> by <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Vice President</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bush</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Conservatives</ENAMEX> say it's a further intrusion on <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">American</ENAMEX> sovereignty. The
